OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1777097136
OL,3,C'I want him to be proud of me' ` MP
OL,4,Crunning London Marathon in brother's
OL,5,Cmemory
OL,7,F"We all think our big brothers are
OL,8,Frock stars, but he actually was," the
OL,9,FLabour MP said.
OL,11,F"I always wanted him to think I was
OL,12,Fcool."
OL,14,FThough a seasoned marathon runner, Mr
OL,15,FFenton-Glynn said he likes to think of
OL,16,Fhimself as a "voice for mediocre
OL,17,Frunners".
OL,19,FHe added: "I think doing something in
OL,20,Fyour outside time is incredibly
OL,21,Fimportant as an MP.
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@aO]sD@AOUtD@FO]xD@NOUyD@HO]{D@
