SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1777097136
OL,3,C'I want him to be proud of me' ` MP
OL,4,Crunning London Marathon in brother's
OL,5,Cmemory
OL,7,FMany of the Sarcoma UK runners are
OL,8,F"notoriously famous for wearing
OL,9,Foutrageous kit, wigs and tutus and so
OL,10,Fon", he said.
OL,12,FBut he plans to opt simply for a T-
OL,13,Fshirt representing the charity,
OL,14,Fadding: "I'm going to be a little bit
OL,15,Fmore conservative, as you might
OL,16,Fexpect."
OL,18,FThe former chancellor, who turns 60 in
OL,19,FNovember, said this year's training
OL,20,Fhas been harder than previous years.
OL,26,@pD@AOUrD@CO]vD@IOUxD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
