OL,3,C'I want him to be proud of me' ` MP
OL,4,Crunning London Marathon in brother's
OL,5,Cmemory
OL,7,FThe foundation is spun out of the club
OL,8,Fand does various things linking the
OL,9,Fclub to the community, including men's
OL,10,Fmental health, inclusive sport `
OL,11,Fincluding pioneering physical
OL,12,Fdisability rugby league ` and keeping
OL,13,Felderly people active.
OL,15,FNorth Shropshire MP Helen Morgan, an
OL,16,Fexperienced half-marathon runner, said
OL,17,Fshe "felt a little bit of the itch of
OL,18,Frunning a long way" when she heard her
OL,19,FLiberal Democrat colleague Wendy
OL,20,FChamberlain was signing up for the
OL,21,Fmarathon.
OL,26,@yD@EOUzD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/20
